cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE

The paper deals with the problem of human behavior understanding in videos, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach is based on unsupervised learning, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves motion estimation and pixel-wise dense prediction, which are topics related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of a GAN-based framework suggests a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
